# CatIntAssist core

- Interpreter reliability > features. Prefer smallest safe diff.
- Transcription + translation ≈ 80% viewport; scoreboard/chrome ≈ 20%. Target 900×600, scale up.
- Version pill always visible (upper right). Feature ships bump `src/App.js` version.
- Laconic replies (see answer-length). On-call brainspace is tiny.
- Do not commit/push unless user says commit/push. Never force-push.
- After feature: test → refactor/cleanup if needed → ship only if confident (no crash).
- Proposed changes: show precisely from → to before large edits.

# Hot paths — do not block or weaken

- STT: `src/hooks/useDeepgram.js` and transcript apply path
- Audio play/route: soundboard / passthrough / `src/utils/audio*`
- Numbers/phones: `src/utils/sensitiveDataProtector.js` — never strip digits while reading

# Stack (do not hallucinate)

- CRA (`react-scripts`), not Vite. No Electron/Tauri shell in this repo.
- Tab capture = `getDisplayMedia`. Phone assistant = mic mode (see onboarding doc).
